# Definitions of Ready and Done

## Definition of Ready

A user story is ready when:

1. It cites at least one baseline identifier (FR-, NFR-) from `_registry/baseline-trace.yaml`.
2. Acceptance criteria include {% for ctrl in compliance_controls %}`{{ ctrl }}`{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %} where applicable.
3. Scope fits inside one sprint ({{ sprint_length_weeks }} weeks).
4. Test oracle is deterministic (pass/fail criterion stated).

## Definition of Done

A user story is done when:

1. Code merged behind review gates defined in `_context/quality-standards.md`.
2. Tests pass, including at least one test case that references the baseline ID.
3. Security review complete (cite `CTRL-*` IDs satisfied).
4. Documentation updated (release notes cite the baseline ID).
5. Deployment steps match `projects/<ProjectName>/06-deployment-operations/runbook.md`.

## Traceability

Every acceptance criterion MUST name a baseline FR-, NFR-, or CTRL- ID.
The kernel's `HybridSyncGate` fails if this file contains no baseline IDs.
